1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,367
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,367 --> 00:00:02,667
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:04,267 --> 00:00:05,467
(Episode 64)

4
00:00:11,967 --> 00:00:13,273
Now I'm even...

5
00:00:14,867 --> 00:00:17,867
hearing things.

6
00:00:33,967 --> 00:00:36,953
<i>Calling "Mom"</i>

7
00:00:38,500 --> 00:00:42,253
<i>I quietly picked and ate them</i>

8
00:00:43,967 --> 00:00:44,967
Yeon Sun.

9
00:01:09,073 --> 00:01:10,073
Yeon Sun.

10
00:01:12,200 --> 00:01:13,200
It's me.

11
00:01:15,260 --> 00:01:16,260
Your mom.

12
00:01:20,467 --> 00:01:22,653
Don't go anywhere. Stay right here.

13
00:01:23,340 --> 00:01:25,767
I will be back to get you soon.

14
00:01:30,220 --> 00:01:31,253
I'm sorry, Yeon Sun.

15
00:01:32,707 --> 00:01:34,040
You've been waiting a long time,
haven't you?

16
00:01:35,920 --> 00:01:37,420
I took too long, didn't I?

17
00:01:40,623 --> 00:01:42,090
What are you saying, ma'am?

18
00:01:42,598 --> 00:01:45,398
Why are you...

19
00:01:47,466 --> 00:01:48,499
I'm sorry, Yeon Sun.

20
00:01:50,367 --> 00:01:53,267
I couldn't recognize you
even when you were right in front of me.

21
00:01:55,224 --> 00:01:56,576
I'm so sorry, sweetheart.

22
00:01:58,567 --> 00:02:02,044
You're my mom?

23
00:02:05,041 --> 00:02:06,041
How can that be?

24
00:02:08,788 --> 00:02:09,855
How could you possibly be...

25
00:02:11,585 --> 00:02:12,585
That's right.

26
00:02:15,031 --> 00:02:17,023
I know it's impossible to believe.

27
00:02:18,038 --> 00:02:19,202
I felt the same way.

28
00:02:21,409 --> 00:02:22,409
Until the other day,

29
00:02:23,655 --> 00:02:26,587
when I saw the burn scar on your leg,

30
00:02:29,484 --> 00:02:31,984
I didn't recognize you,
even with you right in front of me.

31
00:02:34,500 --> 00:02:35,585
I shouldn't be like this.

32
00:02:37,100 --> 00:02:39,267
A mother shouldn't be like this.

33
00:02:43,267 --> 00:02:46,095
Ma'am,

34
00:02:47,100 --> 00:02:49,604
what are you talking about?

35
00:02:50,867 --> 00:02:55,152
How could you possibly be my mom?

36
00:02:55,320 --> 00:02:56,320
Yeon Sun, please.

37
00:02:59,244 --> 00:03:01,277
Just listen to your mom.

38
00:03:09,020 --> 00:03:10,153
You remember, don't you?

39
00:03:12,259 --> 00:03:13,697
The day we parted,

40
00:03:15,700 --> 00:03:19,030
we each kept...

41
00:03:19,030 --> 00:03:21,563
Stop it. Stop.

42
00:03:26,163 --> 00:03:28,063
My mom is dead!

43
00:03:28,966 --> 00:03:31,954
That woman died a long time ago!

44
00:03:33,600 --> 00:03:36,531
Yeon Sun!

45
00:03:36,973 --> 00:03:39,930
Yeon Sun!

46
00:03:47,723 --> 00:03:50,255
Yeon Sun!

47
00:03:59,667 --> 00:04:01,100
Yeon Sun!

48
00:04:07,441 --> 00:04:10,041
What's going on with her?
She's not answering her phone.

49
00:04:12,510 --> 00:04:13,510
- Dad.
- Yeah?

50
00:04:13,510 --> 00:04:15,158
Grandma Sun Bun said...

51
00:04:15,158 --> 00:04:17,547
they definitely came home together
after line dancing.

52
00:04:18,700 --> 00:04:21,685
Then she came home and went out again.

53
00:04:24,867 --> 00:04:25,867
Yes, Grandpa.

54
00:04:26,860 --> 00:04:28,394
What? Grandma?

55
00:04:29,338 --> 00:04:31,597
Okay.
I'll look for her too and let you know.

56
00:04:33,034 --> 00:04:35,813
What's going on?
He can't reach your grandma too?

57
00:04:35,913 --> 00:04:38,633
No, she went out this afternoon
and still hasn't come back.

58
00:04:39,585 --> 00:04:42,048
Do you think they might be together
right now?

59
00:04:42,227 --> 00:04:43,227
Together?

60
00:04:44,200 --> 00:04:45,362
Then maybe they're...

61
00:04:46,129 --> 00:04:47,537
I have a feeling that's where they are.

62
00:04:47,537 --> 00:04:49,390
- Let's go check.
- I'm coming too.

63
00:04:49,391 --> 00:04:51,286
No, Dad. You stay here.

64
00:04:51,467 --> 00:04:53,426
Mom might come home while we're gone.

65
00:04:53,709 --> 00:04:55,640
Okay. Hurry.

66
00:04:58,824 --> 00:05:01,062
Where could she have gone this late?

67
00:05:02,363 --> 00:05:04,267
Do you have any idea where she might be?

68
00:05:04,567 --> 00:05:08,456
Gyeol went to look for her,
so don't worry and go to your room.

69
00:05:09,267 --> 00:05:11,600
Gyeol? Then...

70
00:05:12,113 --> 00:05:14,166
Does Gyeol know where Mother is?

71
00:05:14,167 --> 00:05:16,073
I said go to your room.

72
00:05:16,148 --> 00:05:19,640
Father,
he's just worried about Mother too.

73
00:05:19,641 --> 00:05:20,874
If you keep...

74
00:05:21,967 --> 00:05:23,894
He said go, so just go.

75
00:05:24,467 --> 00:05:28,198
Judging by the Chairman's reaction,
I'm sure she's fine.

76
00:05:28,867 --> 00:05:31,258
What? Do you know something too?

77
00:05:32,167 --> 00:05:33,354
What on earth is going on?

78
00:05:33,355 --> 00:05:35,934
Does everyone know except us?

79
00:05:39,752 --> 00:05:40,819
Seriously.

80
00:05:40,985 --> 00:05:44,159
Are you really that clueless? My goodness.

81
00:05:44,492 --> 00:05:47,286
Yong Man,
I know we've been like brothers...

82
00:05:47,290 --> 00:05:49,390
for over 60 years,
but isn't this a little too much?

83
00:05:49,917 --> 00:05:51,486
I'm still the CEO.

84
00:05:51,731 --> 00:05:53,223
And I'm still Mr. Ju. So what?

85
00:05:55,001 --> 00:05:56,781
Seriously, I can't get through to him.

86
00:05:56,781 --> 00:06:00,879
Why does nobody listen to me these days,
whether at home or at work?

87
00:06:01,224 --> 00:06:02,605
Crystal, I'm going to the room.

88
00:06:05,700 --> 00:06:08,067
I'm steaming.

89
00:06:18,113 --> 00:06:19,955
She's whose mom?

90
00:06:23,056 --> 00:06:24,056
No way.

91
00:06:25,826 --> 00:06:29,027
How could she be my mom? Just how?

92
00:06:43,228 --> 00:06:44,228
Grandma!

93
00:06:48,244 --> 00:06:49,244
Gyeol!

94
00:06:49,637 --> 00:06:50,954
Grandma, are you okay?

95
00:06:51,646 --> 00:06:54,419
Did the two of you meet here?

96
00:06:56,167 --> 00:06:58,033
Yes, we did.

97
00:06:59,709 --> 00:07:01,755
I met my Yeon Sun.

98
00:07:07,628 --> 00:07:08,628
Grandma...

99
00:07:13,157 --> 00:07:14,324
My goodness.

100
00:07:15,767 --> 00:07:19,567
To think Eun Ae is my Yeon Sun's daughter.

101
00:07:24,070 --> 00:07:25,452
Now I understand.

102
00:07:26,666 --> 00:07:29,618
I couldn't stop looking at you,
without even realizing why.

103
00:07:32,200 --> 00:07:34,500
You're the spitting image of your mom.

104
00:07:36,363 --> 00:07:38,385
The spitting image of my Yeon Sun.

105
00:07:40,070 --> 00:07:43,637
I had a feeling I'd find you both here.

106
00:07:46,178 --> 00:07:49,316
Where's my mom?

107
00:07:50,392 --> 00:07:51,598
Hasn't she come home yet?

108
00:07:52,666 --> 00:07:55,990
This isn't good.
She's been gone quite a while.

109
00:07:56,467 --> 00:07:59,867
Maybe she's somewhere trying
to collect herself after such a shock.

110
00:08:00,395 --> 00:08:01,395
I hope so.

111
00:08:02,791 --> 00:08:06,512
Team Manager, take Grandma home first.

112
00:08:06,900 --> 00:08:09,130
Dad and I will keep looking for Mom.

113
00:08:09,767 --> 00:08:12,300
She may have already gone home by now.

114
00:08:12,300 --> 00:08:15,998
All right. I'll take Grandma home,
so you head home too, Eun Ae.

115
00:08:16,452 --> 00:08:18,152
Call me the moment you find your mother.

116
00:08:18,152 --> 00:08:19,252
I will.

117
00:08:20,583 --> 00:08:21,777
What am I going to do?

118
00:08:22,363 --> 00:08:23,430
My Yeon Sun.

119
00:08:24,145 --> 00:08:28,383
I've driven another nail into her heart.

120
00:08:29,139 --> 00:08:31,327
Grandma, let's go home first.

121
00:08:31,800 --> 00:08:33,552
Grandpa's been very worried about you,
okay?

122
00:08:34,488 --> 00:08:35,712
What do I do?

123
00:08:36,958 --> 00:08:37,958
Grandma.

124
00:09:21,867 --> 00:09:23,340
I was afraid this might be true...

125
00:09:25,267 --> 00:09:26,509
She was alive.

126
00:09:30,755 --> 00:09:32,062
I thought
maybe she'd been in an accident...

127
00:09:33,020 --> 00:09:36,044
or had died of an illness
and couldn't come back for me.

128
00:09:39,300 --> 00:09:42,008
Why did you show up?

129
00:09:43,688 --> 00:09:44,962
I believed you were dead.

130
00:09:46,530 --> 00:09:48,251
That you were no longer in this world.

131
00:09:48,539 --> 00:09:51,800
You should've stayed gone
and let me move on.

132
00:09:53,048 --> 00:09:56,515
Why did you show up now? Why now?

133
00:10:17,531 --> 00:10:18,598
Be careful.

134
00:10:21,424 --> 00:10:25,497
Grandma, don't think about anything today.
Just get a good night's sleep.

135
00:10:26,367 --> 00:10:28,185
Okay, I will.

136
00:10:28,621 --> 00:10:30,116
Don't worry too much.

137
00:10:30,800 --> 00:10:33,424
I'll stay by her side.

138
00:10:34,302 --> 00:10:37,609
More importantly, what about Yeon Sun...
I mean, Eun Ae's mom?

139
00:10:37,688 --> 00:10:41,519
Eun Ae and the family are looking for her,
so we should hear from them soon.

140
00:10:41,998 --> 00:10:43,965
I'm sure she'll be fine.

141
00:10:44,967 --> 00:10:48,100
From here on,
we just have to work through everything...

142
00:10:48,423 --> 00:10:50,158
one step at a time,
the way it's meant to be.

143
00:10:50,491 --> 00:10:51,991
Yes, Grandpa. Good night.

144
00:11:01,467 --> 00:11:02,856
My Yeon Sun...

145
00:11:04,167 --> 00:11:07,986
She must be hurting so much right now.
What do I do?

146
00:11:09,771 --> 00:11:12,367
As if all the pain I'd already caused her
wasn't enough,

147
00:11:13,767 --> 00:11:17,713
I ended up breaking her heart
all over again.

148
00:11:18,967 --> 00:11:22,351
Things will get better, little by little.

149
00:11:23,567 --> 00:11:25,949
After carrying all that resentment
for so many years,

150
00:11:26,437 --> 00:11:28,556
how could it possibly disappear overnight?

151
00:11:33,431 --> 00:11:34,431
Mom.

152
00:11:35,767 --> 00:11:38,348
You've been here this whole time?
I had no idea.

153
00:11:38,852 --> 00:11:39,885
Turn off the light.

154
00:11:40,031 --> 00:11:42,526
Come on. Let's go inside.

155
00:11:43,005 --> 00:11:44,916
Dad's been waiting for you.

156
00:11:45,409 --> 00:11:47,869
Let's go inside and talk with Dad, okay?

157
00:11:47,952 --> 00:11:50,119
Talk about what? I have nothing to say.

158
00:11:50,413 --> 00:11:54,533
I can't possibly understand
exactly how you feel right now,

159
00:11:55,109 --> 00:11:58,666
but Grandma spent her whole life
looking for you too.

160
00:11:59,589 --> 00:12:01,989
When I installed
Joy's people-finder app for her,

161
00:12:01,989 --> 00:12:03,505
I could tell
just by the look on her face...

162
00:12:05,967 --> 00:12:09,498
how desperately she wanted to find you.

163
00:12:10,024 --> 00:12:11,783
Stop it. What do you know?

164
00:12:21,167 --> 00:12:23,447
So, what happened?

165
00:12:23,988 --> 00:12:25,552
Do you know why Grandma's being like that?

166
00:12:28,400 --> 00:12:31,066
Your father's asking you something.
Why won't you answer?

167
00:12:31,517 --> 00:12:33,759
Where did you find Grandma?

168
00:12:34,467 --> 00:12:37,816
I think it's best if you hear it
from Grandma and Grandpa later.

169
00:12:39,163 --> 00:12:40,163
Excuse me.

170
00:12:44,013 --> 00:12:45,013
Hey.

171
00:12:46,091 --> 00:12:48,377
Really? I'm glad she's home.

172
00:12:48,723 --> 00:12:51,256
I'll let Grandma know. Bye.

173
00:12:52,663 --> 00:12:55,041
She's home? Who? From where?

174
00:12:55,516 --> 00:12:57,202
I should get going.

175
00:12:58,013 --> 00:13:00,907
Hey, don't we deserve an answer?

176
00:13:01,909 --> 00:13:04,208
What's going on? Why is everyone here?

177
00:13:09,267 --> 00:13:11,622
What's wrong? Did something happen?

178
00:13:11,623 --> 00:13:13,315
What took you so long to get home?

179
00:13:13,316 --> 00:13:15,757
You don't even know
what's been happening in this family.

180
00:13:30,367 --> 00:13:31,367
At least have a glass of water.

181
00:13:40,838 --> 00:13:42,005
You've been through so much, haven't you?

182
00:13:43,600 --> 00:13:46,869
Still, isn't it a blessing
that you've found each other again?

183
00:13:47,491 --> 00:13:48,491
A blessing?

184
00:13:49,873 --> 00:13:51,154
What's so fortunate about this?

185
00:13:51,967 --> 00:13:56,255
I know you're hurt and angry right now,

186
00:13:57,891 --> 00:13:59,751
but deep down...

187
00:13:59,752 --> 00:14:01,679
You should all stop talking.

188
00:14:02,126 --> 00:14:05,075
Please don't act like you know
when you know nothing.

189
00:14:08,598 --> 00:14:10,690
She must have spent years looking for you.

190
00:14:12,341 --> 00:14:15,219
She's spent decades searching for you...

191
00:14:15,514 --> 00:14:16,816
Cho Seong Jun!

192
00:14:24,067 --> 00:14:26,955
What are you talking about?
You finished your assignment?

193
00:14:27,849 --> 00:14:30,270
Honey.

194
00:14:31,049 --> 00:14:33,505
Something I've been holding onto
for so long...

195
00:14:34,100 --> 00:14:36,648
was suddenly resolved in an instant.

196
00:14:38,221 --> 00:14:40,859
It feels a little empty,

197
00:14:42,567 --> 00:14:45,167
but it's also such a relief.

198
00:14:49,828 --> 00:14:51,390
Let go of this. Let's go inside, honey.

199
00:14:52,620 --> 00:14:53,748
- Seung Wu, help your dad.
- Yes?

200
00:14:54,231 --> 00:14:56,198
Seung Ri, put this box in Dad's study.

201
00:14:56,599 --> 00:14:58,260
Get up. Come on.

202
00:14:58,716 --> 00:15:01,388
Dear Father, come this way.

203
00:15:02,967 --> 00:15:04,633
Careful.

204
00:15:12,909 --> 00:15:15,016
Monday at ten. One big one.

205
00:15:16,009 --> 00:15:18,899
Don't forget. If you break your promise,

206
00:15:19,509 --> 00:15:23,118
your life's over. From Jeong Dong Pal.

207
00:15:24,038 --> 00:15:25,038
Jeong Dong Pal?

208
00:15:33,267 --> 00:15:34,267
How's Dad?

209
00:15:35,337 --> 00:15:36,939
He passed out right away.

210
00:15:38,449 --> 00:15:39,790
What on earth happened?

211
00:15:40,023 --> 00:15:41,790
Dad looked really shaken.

212
00:15:43,137 --> 00:15:44,800
Do you know what's going on?

213
00:15:45,300 --> 00:15:47,263
It's probably nothing.
Don't worry about it.

214
00:15:49,634 --> 00:15:50,634
Leave it.

215
00:15:50,934 --> 00:15:54,044
I may not look it,
but I'm a true gentleman.

216
00:16:08,500 --> 00:16:11,973
So Mother finally met Grandma.

217
00:16:13,237 --> 00:16:14,237
How's she holding up?

218
00:16:14,738 --> 00:16:16,869
She's still having a hard time
accepting it.

219
00:16:17,463 --> 00:16:19,230
Mom's trauma runs deep.

220
00:16:19,767 --> 00:16:21,848
They'd met several times already.

221
00:16:22,514 --> 00:16:24,035
How did they not recognize each other?

222
00:16:24,444 --> 00:16:28,422
After all, 50 years is long enough...

223
00:16:29,067 --> 00:16:30,533
to be someone's lifetime.

224
00:16:30,767 --> 00:16:34,180
Wait. Then what about you
and the Team Manager?

225
00:16:34,785 --> 00:16:36,487
Your family relationship...

226
00:16:37,867 --> 00:16:40,866
I know what you're getting at,
but there's no problem between us.

227
00:16:40,935 --> 00:16:42,169
What do you mean?

228
00:16:42,273 --> 00:16:44,159
How could there be no problem?

229
00:16:44,559 --> 00:16:45,559
Team Manager...

230
00:16:47,642 --> 00:16:49,713
Don't waste your time worrying about that.

231
00:16:50,024 --> 00:16:51,740
What the three of us need to do...

232
00:16:51,834 --> 00:16:54,879
is help Mom open her heart to Grandma.

233
00:16:54,880 --> 00:16:56,272
We need to find a way to do that.

234
00:16:56,600 --> 00:16:59,032
Yes, you're right, Eun Ae.

235
00:17:02,382 --> 00:17:03,926
Bit Na, you're awake?

236
00:17:04,463 --> 00:17:06,290
Dad.

237
00:17:09,260 --> 00:17:11,606
You smell funny.

238
00:17:12,366 --> 00:17:15,010
Smell? I just took a shower.

239
00:17:16,635 --> 00:17:19,256
Now that you mention it,
I do smell pain relief patches.

240
00:17:20,134 --> 00:17:22,205
- Is it you?
- What? No.

241
00:17:25,867 --> 00:17:26,867
What's going on, Eun Hyeong?

242
00:17:27,188 --> 00:17:30,755
What were you doing,
hauling bricks instead of teaching?

243
00:17:31,438 --> 00:17:33,287
The thing is...

244
00:17:43,000 --> 00:17:45,783
Kang Yeon Ja,
what do you think you're doing?

245
00:17:46,395 --> 00:17:48,308
Do you even know what time it is?

246
00:17:48,467 --> 00:17:50,741
I'm here to see Madam. Is she home?

247
00:17:52,100 --> 00:17:54,891
Madam? You mean my mother?

248
00:17:58,256 --> 00:17:59,494
Unbelievable.

249
00:18:00,214 --> 00:18:02,801
You barge in first thing in the morning...

250
00:18:03,191 --> 00:18:04,512
and expect to see her?

251
00:18:04,842 --> 00:18:06,655
Why all the commotion?

252
00:18:08,767 --> 00:18:09,767
Is she inside?

253
00:18:13,567 --> 00:18:14,567
Go on in.

254
00:18:15,267 --> 00:18:16,300
Father.

255
00:18:20,200 --> 00:18:22,652
You two stay. I need to talk to you.

256
00:18:28,805 --> 00:18:30,759
Come in and sit down, Yeon Sun.

257
00:18:32,230 --> 00:18:34,448
I didn't come
to sit face-to-face with you.

258
00:18:40,313 --> 00:18:41,313
Here.

259
00:18:44,185 --> 00:18:45,985
My goodness.

260
00:18:48,363 --> 00:18:51,022
You've kept this all this time?

261
00:18:51,967 --> 00:18:54,472
Yes. I couldn't bring myself...

262
00:18:54,473 --> 00:18:56,562
to throw it away.

263
00:18:56,840 --> 00:18:58,440
I'm here to return it
to its rightful owner.

264
00:18:59,024 --> 00:19:00,024
Yeon Sun.

265
00:19:00,948 --> 00:19:03,581
The Yeon Sun you're looking for
no longer exists.

266
00:19:04,067 --> 00:19:06,819
Jang Yeon Sun,
who was abandoned by her own mother...

267
00:19:07,084 --> 00:19:09,568
and passed around like baggage
through adoptions, failed adoptions,

268
00:19:09,776 --> 00:19:11,092
and orphanages, is gone.

269
00:19:11,206 --> 00:19:12,456
My name is Kang Yeon Ja.

270
00:19:12,855 --> 00:19:14,955
I never had a mother to begin with.

271
00:19:17,420 --> 00:19:21,223
I trust I've made myself clear.

272
00:19:22,048 --> 00:19:23,981
- I'm leaving.
- No.

273
00:19:25,742 --> 00:19:29,162
Please. Just listen to me.

274
00:19:30,049 --> 00:19:31,305
Don't touch me.

275
00:19:32,295 --> 00:19:33,495
It makes my skin crawl.

276
00:19:36,388 --> 00:19:38,442
Father.

277
00:19:39,267 --> 00:19:41,448
Is Kang Yeon Ja really Mother's daughter?

278
00:19:42,452 --> 00:19:43,452
Are you certain?

279
00:19:44,923 --> 00:19:46,129
But you know everything already...

280
00:19:48,442 --> 00:19:52,541
Father, how can you be so sure?

281
00:19:53,717 --> 00:19:54,717
What?

282
00:19:54,717 --> 00:19:56,789
A necklace like that...

283
00:19:56,790 --> 00:19:59,108
could've been copied
from something someone heard.

284
00:19:59,507 --> 00:20:02,929
I think you should take a DNA test.

285
00:20:03,367 --> 00:20:05,601
I agree, Father.

286
00:20:06,016 --> 00:20:09,007
What if Mr. Cho and Kang Yeon Ja
planned this all along...

287
00:20:09,008 --> 00:20:10,973
and approached you on purpose?

288
00:20:11,473 --> 00:20:15,033
Whether it's true or not,
getting tested wouldn't hurt.

289
00:20:15,791 --> 00:20:18,744
I happen to know
a very good testing center.

290
00:20:18,957 --> 00:20:20,275
If you leave it to me, I'll...

291
00:20:20,276 --> 00:20:21,417
Ko Dae Chi!

292
00:20:23,743 --> 00:20:25,622
Grandpa, what's wrong?

293
00:20:28,800 --> 00:20:32,305
I stayed up all night thinking about it.

294
00:20:33,349 --> 00:20:36,149
How could I have failed to recognize you?

295
00:20:39,490 --> 00:20:42,179
I never imagined the woman
who abandoned her daughter...

296
00:20:42,366 --> 00:20:43,919
would marry up and become the wife...

297
00:20:43,919 --> 00:20:45,832
of a conglomerate chairman.

298
00:20:46,767 --> 00:20:48,798
Even after hearing
she had a long-lost daughter,

299
00:20:49,409 --> 00:20:51,783
even after seeing
those disgusting flower pancakes...

300
00:20:54,063 --> 00:20:55,841
I guess your wish came true.

301
00:20:57,301 --> 00:21:00,120
I can see why you'd abandon your daughter.

302
00:21:01,267 --> 00:21:03,357
That's not true, Yeon Sun.

303
00:21:03,667 --> 00:21:05,194
Absolutely not.

304
00:21:08,369 --> 00:21:12,149
Back then, you had severe burns,

305
00:21:13,223 --> 00:21:16,323
and I couldn't even afford
your medical treatment.

306
00:21:17,638 --> 00:21:19,527
My precious child was dying,

307
00:21:20,395 --> 00:21:22,859
and I was such a helpless mother.

308
00:21:24,831 --> 00:21:26,550
The Chairman saved you
from those flames...

309
00:21:27,523 --> 00:21:30,780
and took responsibility for you
until the end. He was my savior.

310
00:21:33,399 --> 00:21:37,461
So you could get a proper education
and be raised well...

311
00:21:37,816 --> 00:21:41,907
So you're saying you married
into a better life because of me?

312
00:21:41,907 --> 00:21:43,307
Is that what you're saying?

313
00:21:45,223 --> 00:21:46,788
There's nothing more to say.

314
00:21:48,323 --> 00:21:51,748
I'm not a seven-year-old girl who thought
she'd die without her mom anymore.

315
00:21:52,981 --> 00:21:55,455
I'll be 60 before long.

316
00:21:57,820 --> 00:22:01,367
Don't ever let me see you again.

317
00:22:01,767 --> 00:22:02,767
Do you understand?

318
00:22:04,084 --> 00:22:07,114
No! Yeon Sun!

319
00:22:09,534 --> 00:22:12,122
Yeon Sun!

320
00:22:13,523 --> 00:22:14,523
- Yeon Sun.
- I'll go after them.

321
00:22:14,800 --> 00:22:16,334
- Stay here.
- Father.

322
00:22:16,467 --> 00:22:18,068
Dad, don't do anything.

323
00:22:19,803 --> 00:22:21,913
That ticking time bomb finally exploded.

324
00:22:22,323 --> 00:22:23,815
I'm losing my mind.

325
00:22:25,067 --> 00:22:27,107
Yeon Sun, please!

326
00:22:27,802 --> 00:22:29,234
Please listen to me.

327
00:22:30,121 --> 00:22:32,862
I never abandoned you.

328
00:22:32,863 --> 00:22:34,255
Let go of me.

329
00:22:36,313 --> 00:22:37,313
Yeon Sun.

330
00:22:38,674 --> 00:22:39,674
Yeon Sun!

331
00:22:47,428 --> 00:22:50,028
This is all my fault.

332
00:22:51,356 --> 00:22:55,455
Back then, my parents told me
to leave her child behind.

333
00:22:56,663 --> 00:23:00,002
I planned to marry first
and come back for you right away.

334
00:23:01,091 --> 00:23:03,151
But then my mother suffered a stroke.

335
00:23:03,800 --> 00:23:05,367
She passed away a month later.

336
00:23:06,267 --> 00:23:10,025
After the funeral,
we went back for you, but...

337
00:23:11,667 --> 00:23:15,515
That's quite a heartbreaking story.

338
00:23:16,516 --> 00:23:18,149
Whatever happened back then,

339
00:23:19,267 --> 00:23:21,059
it has nothing to do with me anymore.

340
00:23:22,523 --> 00:23:24,288
- I'll be going now.
- Please.

341
00:23:26,495 --> 00:23:28,528
Don't blame your mother alone.

342
00:23:29,773 --> 00:23:33,042
She was barely living all those years.

343
00:23:33,891 --> 00:23:36,813
She spent her whole life longing for you.

344
00:23:49,634 --> 00:23:52,287
Did it hurt badly, mister?

345
00:23:54,067 --> 00:23:55,067
I'm sorry.

346
00:23:55,800 --> 00:23:58,559
No. It didn't hurt at all.

347
00:23:59,867 --> 00:24:03,969
I'm just so happy you've gotten healthy,
Yeon Sun.

348
00:24:06,367 --> 00:24:09,440
I won't ask you to forgive us.

349
00:24:10,167 --> 00:24:14,702
But please let go of your hatred
for your mother.

350
00:24:16,009 --> 00:24:17,393
I'm begging you, Yeon Sun.

351
00:24:20,117 --> 00:24:24,055
I don't hate her.

352
00:24:25,567 --> 00:24:29,034
Hatred only exists
when there's still something left to feel.

353
00:24:30,338 --> 00:24:34,222
Just as we lived not knowing each other
for the past 50 years,

354
00:24:34,223 --> 00:24:36,334
let's keep living that way.

355
00:24:38,195 --> 00:24:39,462
Don't ever look for me again.

356
00:24:40,903 --> 00:24:42,487
Yeon Sun.

357
00:24:43,190 --> 00:24:44,287
Honey!

358
00:24:46,609 --> 00:24:48,676
I'll see that she gets home.
You two should go inside.

359
00:25:06,074 --> 00:25:09,962
Honey, what happened?
Where have you been all morning?

360
00:25:10,755 --> 00:25:11,988
She came to our house.

361
00:25:11,988 --> 00:25:13,788
She's back from seeing Grandma.

362
00:25:14,709 --> 00:25:15,990
I see.

363
00:25:16,783 --> 00:25:19,344
Did things go well
between you and Grandma, Mom?

364
00:25:19,981 --> 00:25:20,981
Grandma?

365
00:25:24,681 --> 00:25:25,681
Team Manager Ko.

366
00:25:26,745 --> 00:25:28,779
I'm sorry, but I need you to move out.

367
00:25:29,059 --> 00:25:30,059
Sorry?

368
00:25:30,500 --> 00:25:34,473
Your lease still has three months left,
but I have no choice.

369
00:25:34,874 --> 00:25:37,961
I'll pay the penalty, so move out today.

370
00:25:38,189 --> 00:25:39,189
Mom.

371
00:25:39,752 --> 00:25:40,952
Honey, don't be like this.

372
00:25:40,952 --> 00:25:43,144
He didn't do anything wrong.

373
00:25:43,549 --> 00:25:46,348
The woman who abandoned me
to marry into a better life...

374
00:25:47,237 --> 00:25:50,740
suddenly showed up 50 years later,
claiming to be my mother.

375
00:25:53,462 --> 00:25:54,894
How can I...

376
00:25:55,784 --> 00:25:58,155
live under the same roof with her grandson
as if nothing happened?

377
00:25:58,156 --> 00:25:59,523
I can't do it.

378
00:26:02,113 --> 00:26:04,977
Goodness gracious,
what are you talking about?

379
00:26:06,981 --> 00:26:10,901
If Team Manager Ko
is Yeon Ja's mom's grandson,

380
00:26:10,902 --> 00:26:12,452
then the Chairman's wife...

381
00:26:17,800 --> 00:26:20,167
Honey!

382
00:26:20,467 --> 00:26:22,958
Grandma, I'll explain everything later.

383
00:26:22,962 --> 00:26:25,980
My goodness. I'm so shocked.

384
00:26:26,187 --> 00:26:29,387
This is soybean soup.
Have noodles for lunch, okay?

385
00:26:29,883 --> 00:26:31,394
Okay, thanks, Grandma.

386
00:26:31,395 --> 00:26:34,269
Goodness gracious!

387
00:27:07,449 --> 00:27:09,087
You asked my dad for money, right?

388
00:27:11,200 --> 00:27:13,126
My cellmate sure has a loose tongue.

389
00:27:14,113 --> 00:27:15,752
Already?

390
00:27:16,517 --> 00:27:18,484
He ran straight to his daughter?

391
00:27:18,720 --> 00:27:22,253
If you keep this up, I'll report you
for false accusation and blackmail.

392
00:27:23,856 --> 00:27:25,472
Now, let's see.

393
00:27:26,267 --> 00:27:30,651
A false accusation means
making up something that isn't true.

394
00:27:31,367 --> 00:27:32,367
So what exactly did I make up?

395
00:27:34,300 --> 00:27:36,770
Is calling an ex-convict an ex-convict
a false accusation?

396
00:27:36,931 --> 00:27:38,804
- Excuse me?
- Your dad...

397
00:27:39,113 --> 00:27:41,638
and I were prison buddies 25 years ago.

398
00:27:42,637 --> 00:27:44,862
We shared the same cell for five years.

399
00:27:45,749 --> 00:27:48,016
I'll report you right away,
so you'd better be ready.

400
00:27:48,280 --> 00:27:49,280
Report me?

401
00:27:53,667 --> 00:27:55,267
Listen, young lady.

402
00:27:57,359 --> 00:27:58,926
Your dad's a murderer.

403
00:27:59,667 --> 00:28:01,367
He killed someone.

404
00:28:12,467 --> 00:28:15,267
(Our Happy Days)

405
00:28:15,645 --> 00:28:16,826
You want a showdown?

406
00:28:16,827 --> 00:28:18,273
Let's meet right now.

407
00:28:18,274 --> 00:28:20,419
You were the one who wanted to meet.

408
00:28:20,420 --> 00:28:22,705
Hey, you jerks!

409
00:28:24,634 --> 00:28:26,126
What's wrong, Team Manager?

410
00:28:26,127 --> 00:28:27,200
Hang in there!

411
00:28:30,667 --> 00:28:32,400
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
